The paper discusses the limits of deterministic compressed sensing, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of orthonormal basis for sparsity is also a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper may involve numerical analysis (cs.NA) as it deals with the reconstruction of signals using sampling functions.
